HEADWORD: Hallux
<hw>Hal"lux</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧l"l⟦ucr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>hallex</ets>, <ets>allex</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The first, or preaxial, digit of the hind limb,
corresponding to the pollux in the fore limb; the great toe; the hind
toe of birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hallway</ent>⟦br⟧
